{"task":"transcribe","language":"english","duration":30.0,"text":"The middle class in towns, however, was burdened by the cost of civil obligations. After the second century, while portrait busts of emperors were being turned out in increasing numbers, there were fewer and fewer local inscriptions. Townspeople could no longer afford them. Small peasant proprietors lost their holdings, attaching themselves as tenants to large estates. Commerce declined due to the unsafe nature of the countryside and the seas. The Roman Empire was in a crisis in which its survival was imperiled.","segments":[{"id":0,"seek":0,"start":0.0,"end":4.239999771118164,"text":" The middle class in towns, however, was burdened by the cost of civil obligations.","tokens":[50364,440,2808,1508,294,18104,11,4461,11,390,12578,292,538,264,2063,295,5605,26234,13,50633],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2097218781709671,"compression_ratio":1.6433823108673096,"no_speech_prob":0.000579219195060432},{"id":1,"seek":0,"start":5.320000171661377,"end":9.619999885559082,"text":" After the second century, while portrait busts of emperors were being turned out in increasing","tokens":[50633,2381,264,1150,4901,11,1339,17126,19432,82,295,846,610,830,645,885,3574,484,294,5662,50850],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2097218781709671,"compression_ratio":1.6433823108673096,"no_speech_prob":0.000579219195060432},{"id":2,"seek":0,"start":9.619999885559082,"end":12.5,"text":" numbers, there were fewer and fewer local inscriptions.","tokens":[50850,3547,11,456,645,13366,293,13366,2654,1028,34173,13,51062],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2097218781709671,"compression_ratio":1.6433823108673096,"no_speech_prob":0.000579219195060432},{"id":3,"seek":0,"start":13.699999809265137,"end":15.260000228881836,"text":" Townspeople could no longer afford them.","tokens":[51062,15954,7053,548,727,572,2854,6157,552,13,51174],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2097218781709671,"compression_ratio":1.6433823108673096,"no_speech_prob":